1. autoptic-ui: Gateway API with Ingress Fallback
values.yaml - Added new ui.gateway block (enabled by default) with:

createGateway: false - render optional Gateway resource
parentRefs - reference to existing Gateway
hostnames, rules - HTTPRoute matching rules
listeners, annotations - optional Gateway configuration
Added fallback comment to ui.ingress section
templates/httproute.yaml - New template for Gateway API HTTPRoute with fail-fast validation

templates/gateway.yaml - New template for optional Gateway resource (rendered when createGateway: true)

templates/ingress.yaml - Added header comment noting it's the fallback path

Environment values files (values-dev.yaml, values-dev-updated.yaml, values-staging.yaml):

Added gateway.enabled: false to maintain mutual exclusivity with existing ingress.enabled: true
2. vectors-helm: Enhanced PVC Configuration
values.yaml - Extended metrics.persistence with:

accessMode: ReadWriteOnce - configurable access mode
annotations: {} - PVC metadata annotations
selector: {} - for pre-provisioned PV binding
volumeName: "" - optional static PV binding
templates/pvc-metrics.yaml - Updated to consume all new fields while maintaining backwards compatibility with defaults

Key Behaviors
Mutual Exclusion: The chart fails fast if both ui.ingress.enabled and ui.gateway.enabled are true
Default Routing: New deployments use Gateway API (HTTPRoute) by default
Ingress Reactivation: Set ui.gateway.enabled: false and ui.ingress.enabled: true to revert to Ingress
PVC Backwards Compatibility: All new PVC fields have defaults matching previous hardcoded values